Happy Love Day or whateva 😏

*3 month update for you guys* This journey will have you going through ups and downs, a whole ass emotional roller coaster. This is me just being transparent about my personal journey and to tell you that this hasn’t been easy for me. I’ve had major stalls to no weight loss some weeks. At times, I really feel like giving up. But i remember that this isn’t a race. This is a whole new way of living that I have to learn and adjust to. Despite it all, I will keep pushing through and continue trusting the process.

I’m hyped y’all! Why? I start therapy this week 😱! I’m going through many emotions for my upcoming appointment from anxiety, fear, excitement and more. 

Despite all of that, I can honestly say that I’m ready! Ready for the journey, the tears, the healing and clarity. I’m blessed to be in a space where I am aware of my mental health and areas that need attention.

*Just a lil reminder during the holidays*

Listen baby, we have tiny tummies now! Sometimes it’s hard for others to understand this new journey that you’re on, especially when it comes to the amount of food we can intake after #wls. Don’t let anyone “guilt” you into putting more on your plate or even try to convince you to eat more. It’s ok to say “no” or “no thank you”. #vsg #justthoughts #vsgfacts #vsgjourney #beforeandafter #vsgsupport
